\begin_inset Formula $\vec{s}$
\end_inset

-degree is a special case of the 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{H}$
\end_inset

-degree from 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "BL1997"

\end_inset

, where in this case 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{H}=x^{\vec{s}}$
\end_inset

.
 As in the uniform shift case, we say a matrix is 
\emph on

\begin_inset Formula $\vec{s}$
\end_inset

-column reduced
\emph default
 or 
\emph on

\begin_inset Formula $\vec{s}$
\end_inset

-reduced
\emph default
 if its 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{s}$
\end_inset

